It is the sense of Congress that—

(1) military-connected children and adolescents, including those caring for or living with wounded, ill, or injured service members or veterans, experience elevated rates of mental health crises, self-harm, and suicidal ideation;

(2) these youth, often referred to as “Hidden Helpers,” frequently rely on the Veteran/Military Suicide and Crisis Line for counseling and crisis support;

